@node "intro" "What is Crypt?"
Crypt is a program that encrypts any data file with a password, so nobody
can't get to the data except the ones who should.

I know there are a lot of other such programs, using much safer algorhythms
than mine, but I wanted a real simple program, no complicated parameters,
options, key-rings and stuff.

The algorhythm used is pretty simple, so if someone really wants your data
bad, he could crack it. However, if you're not sending top-secret classified
inteligence information, or things like that, I think that just seeing the
file being encrypted will be enough to put off any nosy hackers.
@endnode

@node "usage" "How to use Crypt?"
Copy the file "crypt" somewhere in your path. I recommend your C:
directory.

Then just type in a shell window:

@{b}crypt [infile] [password]@{ub}

The program will make a new file with .crpt appended to the name of the
original file.

This new file is the encrypted data. To decrypt it just run the program on
it again with the same password.

You could also make a button in Directory Opus for crypt, so you can just
select the files, and push the button....
@endnode

@node "legal" "It's free."
Crypt is @{b}freeware@{ub}. You are allowed to use it and copy it all you want.

However, you must not change the program in any way... If you @{u}DO@{uu} change it,
please don't mention my name anywhere asocciated with that changed version.

Allthough this program is free, I'd like to let you know, that I am just
another poor student, and any donations would be more than welcome to my
@{" address " link "addy" 0}.
@endnode

@node "future" "WHat's nex what's nex't what's n-x-e-t..."
If I ever write another version of this proggy, I will add one of these
things:

 * More crypting algorhythms. (IDEA, rot13, plus some special ones...)
 * A nice and simple GUI.
 * Support for executable files.
 * Special format for encrypted files. 
 * Recognising encrypted files, and what algorhythm is used.

If you'd like to see the next version with some of these features, please
send moral support to this @{" address " link "addy" 0} . (I wouldn't mind if you had some
extra cash to spare though:).
@endnode

